-- 
Sony to Distribute 23rd James Bond Film With MGM Studio

-- B y   R o n a l d   G r o v e r
-- 
2011-04-14T00:18:59Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-13/sony-to-distribute-23rd-james-bond-film-in-accord-with-mgm.html
Sony Corp. (6758)  reached an agreement to
co-finance and distribute the next James Bond movie for Metro-
Goldwyn-Mayer Studios Inc., extending a relationship for one of
the longest-running film franchises.  The accord also includes the rights to distribute a
subsequent Bond movie, the companies said in a statement today.  The next Bond film, the 23rd installment, will be released
on Nov. 9, 2012. The most recent Bond movie, “Quantum of
Solace,” was released in 2008 and took in $577 million
worldwide, the companies said. The film, starring Daniel Craig
as the British spy, cost $200 million to make, according to
researcher  Box Office Mojo .  The two studios also agreed to “explore co-financing
opportunities” on films produced over the next five years.  “Dr. No,” the first Bond title, was released in 1962,
according to website  IMDB .  To contact the reporter on this story:
